wiki_catalogs.name: Project Overview
wiki_catalogs.prompt: Create comprehensive content for this section focused on the APP-STRUKTUR-BLACKBOX project. Explain its purpose as a structural engineering analysis and visualization system with compliance to SNI and international standards. Describe the application's primary capabilities including structural design, static and dynamic analysis, 3D/2D visualization, standards integration, and educational features. Document the component-based React architecture, TypeScript foundation, and key technical decisions. Include high-level diagrams illustrating the system architecture and data flow. Provide context on target users (engineers, students, educators) and common use cases. Highlight the integration between educational content and practical analysis tools. Discuss the evolution of the codebase as evidenced by backup files and versioned systems. Explain how the application supports both quick analysis tasks and in-depth structural design workflows.

wiki_catalogs.prompt: Develop detailed content for this sub-feature focused on the Design Integration module within the Structural Analysis System. Address common issues such as state synchronization between design modules and the main system, and provide solutions for handling duplicate or conflicting element definitions. Make content accessible to beginners while providing sufficient technical depth for experienced developers regarding component composition and state propagation patterns.

Provide guidance on when to use each analyzer variant based on model size and complexity.

wiki_overview.content:
<blog>
# Comprehensive Project Analysis: Structural Analysis System

## 1. Project Introduction

### Purpose Statement
The Structural Analysis System is a comprehensive web application designed for structural engineering professionals and students to design, analyze, and visualize building structures. The application provides a complete workflow from structural element design through analysis and visualization, with a strong focus on compliance with both Indonesian (SNI) and international structural design standards.

### Core Goals and Objectives
- Provide an intuitive interface for structural element design (beams, columns, slabs)
- Implement a robust structural analysis engine using the stiffness matrix method
- Offer advanced 3D and 2D visualization capabilities for structural models
- Ensure compliance with SNI and international standards (ACI, AISC, Eurocode, ASCE)
- Support educational use with interactive tutorials and example problems
- Enable export of structure data, analysis results, and visualizations

### Target Audience
- Structural engineering students and professors
- Professional structural engineers
- Civil engineering consultants
- Construction project managers
- Academic institutions teaching structural engineering

## 2. Technical Architecture

### Component Breakdown
The application follows a modular architecture with clearly defined components organized by functionality:

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[StructuralAnalysisSystem] --> B[Design Modules]
    A --> C[Analysis Engine]
    A --> D[Visualization]
    A --> E[Standards Integration]
    A --> F[Educational Portal]
    B --> B1[Beam Design]
    B --> B2[Column Design]
    B --> B3[Slab Design]
    C --> C1[Static Analysis]
    C --> C2[Dynamic Analysis]
    D --> D1[3D Viewer]
    D --> D2[2D Drawing]
    E --> E1[SNI Standards]
    E --> E2[International Standards]
    F --> F1[Tutorial Guide]
    F --> F2[Theory Reference]
    F --> F3[Example Problems]
```

### Design Patterns
The application implements several key design patterns:

- **Component-Based Architecture**: React components for UI elements with clear separation of concerns
- **State Management**: Centralized state management within the main application component
- **Modular Design**: Features organized into distinct modules (analysis, design, drawing, standards)
- **Type Safety**: Comprehensive TypeScript interfaces for data structures
- **Event-Driven Communication**: Parent-child component communication through callback functions

### System Relationships
The system components interact through well-defined interfaces:

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    App[StructuralAnalysisSystem] --> Design[Design Modules]
    App --> Analysis[Analysis Engine]
    App --> Visualization[3D/2D Viewers]
    App --> Standards[StandardIntegration]
    Design --> App
    Analysis --> App
    Visualization --> App
    Standards --> App
    App --> Export[ExportManager]
    App --> Educational[EducationalPortal]
```

### Data Flow
The application follows a unidirectional data flow pattern:

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    User[User Input] --> Design[Design Modules]
    Design --> State[Application State]
    State --> Analysis[Analysis Engine]
    Analysis --> Results[Analysis Results]
    State --> Visualization[3D/2D Viewers]
    Results --> UI[User Interface]
    UI --> User
    Standards --> State
    State --> Export[ExportManager]
```

Sources:
- [README.md](d:\1. KERJO\Website\APP-STRUKTUR-BLACKBOX\README.md)
- [StructuralAnalysisSystem.tsx](d:\1. KERJO\Website\APP-STRUKTUR-BLACKBOX\src\structural-analysis\StructuralAnalysisSystem.tsx)

## 3. Key Implementation

### Main Entry Points
- **Application Entry**: `src/main.tsx` - Vite application entry point
- **Main Component**: `src/structural-analysis/StructuralAnalysisSystem.tsx` - Primary application component
- **App Wrapper**: `src/App.tsx` - Root component with educational portal toggle

### Core Modules
- **Design Modules**: `src/structural-analysis/design/` - Beam, column, and slab design calculators
- **Analysis Engine**: `src/structural-analysis/analysis/` - Static and dynamic analysis algorithms
- **Visualization**: `src/structural-analysis/` - 3D viewer and 2D drawing components
- **Standards**: `src/standards/` - SNI and international standard implementations
- **Educational**: `src/educational/` - Tutorial, theory, and example components

### Configuration Approach
The application uses a combination of configuration files and in-code settings:

- **Build Configuration**: `vite.config.ts` - Vite build settings
- **TypeScript Configuration**: `tsconfig.json` - TypeScript compiler options
- **Styling Configuration**: `tailwind.config.js` - Tailwind CSS settings
- **Package Management**: `package.json` - Dependencies and scripts
- **Testing Configuration**: `vitest.config.ts` - Testing framework settings

### External Dependencies
The application leverages several key external libraries:

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[React] --> B[React DOM]
    A --> C[React Three Fiber]
    C --> D[Three.js]
    E[Radix UI] --> F[Dialog, Slider, Switch]
    G[Recharts] --> H[Data Visualization]
    I[Lucide React] --> J[Icons]
    K[React Hook Form] --> L[Form Management]
    M[Zod] --> N[Form Validation]
    O[JSZip] --> P[Export Functionality]
```

- [vite.config.ts](
